# PMOMax Component Changes Summary

This document lists the exact changes made to six key files in the `components` folder, including code snippets for each change.

---

## 1. Header.tsx
**Changes:**
- Added a "User Guide" button to the top-right, styled and accessible.
- Updated props to support opening the User Guide modal.

**Code Snippet:**
```tsx
<button
  onClick={onUserGuide}
  className="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-md border border-brand-border bg-brand-panel hover:bg-brand-border text-sm"
  aria-label="Open User Guide"
>
  <HelpIcon className="w-5 h-5 mr-1" /> User Guide
</button>
```

---

## 2. UserGuideModal.tsx (new file)
**Changes:**
- Created a modal component for the full User Manual.
- Included headings, table of contents, icons, and responsive design.
- Ensured accessibility (keyboard navigation, Escape to close, ARIA attributes).

**Code Snippet:**
```tsx
export const UserGuideModal = ({ open, onClose }) => (
  <div role="dialog" aria-modal="true" ...>
    <header>
      <h2>User Manual</h2>
      <button onClick={onClose} aria-label="Close">×</button>
    </header>
    <nav> {/* Table of Contents */} </nav>
    <section> {/* Manual Content with icons/headings */} </section>
  </div>
);
```

---

## 3. MainContent.tsx
**Changes:**
- Removed the ❓ User Guide reference from the middle panel.
- Enhanced the welcome/empty state with icons, bullet points, and contextual help buttons for each major section.
- Improved visual excitement and intuitiveness.

**Code Snippet:**
```tsx
// Removed old ❓ User Guide button
// Added contextual help buttons and icons to each section
<button onClick={() => onHelp?.('objectives')} ...>?</button>
```

---

## 4. AIAssistantPanel.tsx
**Changes:**
- Updated error messaging to reference `gemini-2.0-flash`.
- Ensured error messages are clear and actionable.

**Code Snippet:**
```tsx
<div>
  {error && (
    <div>
      Error: Gemini model (gemini-2.0-flash) unavailable. Please check your API key.
    </div>
  )}
</div>
```

---

## 5. HelpModal.tsx
**Changes:**
- Ensured modal accessibility: keyboard navigation, Escape to close, ARIA attributes.

**Code Snippet:**
```tsx
<div
  role="dialog"
  aria-modal="true"
  aria-labelledby="help-modal-title"
  ...
>
  <button onClick={onClose} ...>
    <X className="w-5 h-5" />
    <span className="sr-only">Close</span>
  </button>
</div>
```

